KwaZulu-Natal Police are investigating a case of murder after a man was shot and killed in Thokozani in the Albert Falls area this morning. According to Netcare 911, the emergency service received a call about a male who was lying on the floor at a place of his residences. Netcare 911 Spokesperson Shawn Herbst said upon arrival at the place they found that a man had sustained two gunshot wounds to his head. “There was no sign of life and was declared dead by the paramedic who attended to the scene,” Herbst said. KwaZulu-Natal Police spokesperson Thembeka Mbhele said at this stage, no one has been arrested in connection with the shooting. Mbhele said she was not in a position to speculate as to what may have led to the shooting and the police were calling on anyone with information to come forward. “Anyone who has information that can help us solve this case can contact their nearest police station or call Crime Stop on 08600 10111 or SMS Crime Line on 32211,” Mbhele said. -Afro Reporter